This paper deals with the problem of one-bit compressive sensing, which involves quantizing measurements to one bit. This is a problem that falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the recovery of sparse high-dimensional vectors, which is a problem in data structures (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SP). Finally, the paper mentions the use of a combinatorial object known as Union Free Families, which is a topic in mathematics and theoretical computer science (cs.MM).
